cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new modal logic and discusses its properties and decidability. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the expressive power of the logic and its ability to capture temporal relations, which is relevant to AI applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of the satisfiability problem for the logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility for the same reason as cs.DS. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a formal logic and its syntax and semantics.
